WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:09.000
London is the biggest city in Britain. It also has the largest population. After London,

00:09.000 --> 00:15.000
Birmingham is the second largest city, with around 4 million people living and working

00:15.000 --> 00:23.000
there. There are a lot of small cities, such as Oxford and Cambridge. They are beautiful,

00:23.000 --> 00:29.000
and they have two of the oldest universities in the world. Cambridge is the nearest to

00:29.000 --> 00:38.000
London. The most expensive city is London, but it's also the most interesting. London is on the

00:38.000 --> 00:45.000
river Thames and has the most popular places for sightseeing, such as Big Ben, Buckingham Palace,

00:45.000 --> 00:47.000
and Tower Bridge.

